50|$|While {{some people}} were punished severely, others were let off on a milder {{sentence}} such as paying heavy fines or being exiled from their towns. Notable members who were exiled to Mexico were Pedro Balunguit, Pintonggatan, Felipe Salonga, Calao, and Agustin Manuguit. Balanguit was charged with six <b>years</b> <b>of</b> exile and <b>payment</b> <b>of</b> six tael of orejas gold, Pintonggatan with two years, Salonga with eight years, Calao with four years, and Manuguit with six <b>years</b> <b>of</b> exile and <b>payment</b> <b>of</b> 20 tael of orejas gold.|$|R
